edu.eur.absa.model

Class Span

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.eur.absa.model.DataEntity
      • edu.eur.absa.model.Span
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<DataEntity>, java.lang.Iterable<Word>, java.util.Collection<Word>, java.util.NavigableSet<Word>, java.util.Set<Word>, java.util.SortedSet<Word>

    public class Span
extends DataEntity
implements java.util.NavigableSet<Word>
    A Span is an arbitrary sequence of Words that are directly adjacent to one another. Hence, they have to originate from the same textual unit. A Span is the vehicle to add annotations to your textual data. Spans cannot span over multiple textual units as these are by definition independent textual units.
    Author:
    Kim Schouten

      • Span

        public Span(java.lang.String spanType,
            Word firstWord,
            Word lastWord)
     throws IllegalSpanException
        Standard constructor to create a Span object. Note that all words that are contained in a single Span have to originate from the same textual unit.
        Parameters:
        spanType - A textual label denoting the kind of Span. Some basic ones would be "word", "sentence", "aspect", etc.
        firstWord -
        lastWord -
        Throws:
        IllegalSpanException - If the first and last word do not originate from the textual unit.

      • Span

        public Span(java.lang.String spanType,
            Dataset dataset)
        Special 'empty' Span constructor. This is used to create an empty Span for a new textual unit, since no Words are yet added to it. This Span is its own textual unit so this constructor sets textualUnit=this. This constructor will automatically register this span with its parent Dataset.
        Parameters:
        spanType -

      • Span

        public Span(java.lang.String spanType,
            Span textualUnit)
        Special 'empty' Span constructor. This is used to create an empty sub-Span for an existing textual unit that has no Words yet. This can be useful if the given dataset already splits the text into sentences or other sub-blocks of an integral piece of text, but does not provide the word splits. This constructor will automatically register this span with its parent Dataset.
        Parameters:
        spanType -

      • getStrictlyLeftSpans

        public java.util.TreeSet<Span> getStrictlyLeftSpans(java.util.TreeSet<Span> spans)
        Given a TreeSet of Span objects, return the ones that contain only Words that have a lower word order than any word in this instance of Span. The returned set of Spans would appear earlier, or to the left, of the text covered by the current Span, without any overlap.
